        "ggaz-KLLNhJ_text": "<p>Alright, let’s cut through the fluff—getting yourself a DTG printer isn’t just about creativity, it’s a legit business power move. Seriously, once you actually crunch the numbers, the profit potential slaps way harder than most people expect.Here’s what’s up:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>● Less Wastage, Higher Profits. </strong>When you stop ordering tees by the truckload and only print what actually sells, you’re not sitting on stacks of unsold shirts collecting dust (and burning through your cash). And if you toss in stuff like personalized names, dates, whatever—the average order price starts climbing. No joke, you’ll probably be pocketing more per sale vs. those massive bulk deals.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>● Build Your ROI?</strong> It doesn’t have to be rocket science:</p><p>○ Figure out what you’re making right now on each shirt.</p><p>○ Add whatever extra you can charge for that sweet personalized <a href=\"https://www.procolored.com/collections/dtg-printer\" target=\"_blank\"><u>DTG printing</u></a> action.</p><p>○ Ballpark how many more orders you can grab monthly (think pop-up events, company swag, small collab runs).</p><p>○ Knock off materials and labor—inks, blanks, pretreat, all that jazz.</p><p>○ See what’s left, and decide if it’s covering the cost to buy the printer and keep it running.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>● Wanna track if it’s working?</strong> Watch your KPIs: how many prints a day, your cost per tee, how quick you’re turning out orders, repeat customers, returns , and what you’re pocketing on each sale after all the bills.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>● Smart Financing &amp; Risk Management</strong>. Not ready to go all in? Start small. Grab a single Procolored DTG printing unit and a few test blanks, see if people demand it. Preorders are your friend—get cash up front, fund the printer, barely any risk.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>DTG printing brings more than pretty shirts—it involves less risk, faster production, and way more numbers per customer.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Long story short: get yourself a Procolored <a href=\"https://www.procolored.com/collections/dtg-printer\" target=\"_blank\"><u>DTG printing</u></a> setup, and you’re not just pressing designs… you’re leveling up the entire game.</p>",
