        "ggtfPp7M6vA_text": "<p><a href=\"https://www.procolored.com/blogs/news/tagged/industry-trends\" target=\"_blank\">industry trends</a></p><p><a href=\"https://www.procolored.com/blogs/news/tagged/maintenance\" target=\"_blank\">maintenance</a></p><p><a href=\"https://www.procolored.com/blogs/news/tagged/newsroom\" target=\"_blank\">newsroom</a></p><p><a href=\"https://www.procolored.com/blogs/news/tagged/product-showroom\" target=\"_blank\">product showroom</a></p><p><a href=\"https://www.procolored.com/blogs/review\" target=\"_blank\">printer review</a></p>",
        "ggxd2et8iir_text": "<p>Every single time you toss new tech into your business mix, people start with the questions. Sometimes it’s real curiosity, sometimes it’s just pure skepticism.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>So, let’s get brutally honest about the top concerns with <a href=\"https://www.procolored.com/collections/dtg-printer\" target=\"_blank\"><u>DTG printing</u></a>, and why Procolored doesn’t leave you hanging.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><i><strong>● “DTG Prints Don’t Last.”</strong></i></p><p>It all comes down to how you do the thing. If you nail the prep and the curing, those DTG prints aren’t going anywhere. Toss them in the wash, over and over, and the colors stick around. A Procolored DTG printing machine makes this dead simple to show off, too—just share a wash-tested sample, and let the vibrancy do the talking.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><i><strong>● “It’s Too Pricey To Keep Up.”</strong></i></p><p>On the surface? Sure, a DTG printer looks like a big investment. But start comparing the numbers: outsourcing fees, minimum orders, unsold boxes of tees… Suddenly, DTG’s looking way less scary. With Procolored, maintenance is low-key, because they’ve got features that take you on a full stress-free mode.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><i><strong>● “Colors Won’t Match.”</strong></i></p><p>This one is a legit concern—-especially for retailers who need brand consistency. Luckily, you don’t have to panic. Procolored’s got pro-level RIP software, ICC profiles, and rock-solid color management tools to turn chaos into consistency. Red isn’t just “kinda red”—it’s the same shade every single time. Whether it’s your first batch or your thousandth.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><i><strong>● “DTG Only Works On Cotton.”</strong></i></p><p>Sure, cotton’s where it shines—but it’s not the entire playground. Grab the right pre-treatments and some finishing smarts, and watch, you’re printing on blends, even some poly fabrics. So instead of a brick wall, think of this as an excuse to unleash new products. Win-win.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Knock down people’s doubts with proof—real-life, touch-and-see samples. Show, don’t just tell. That way, you’re not just easing minds… you’re actually flipping the script and turning customer fears into trust. And let’s be real, reliability like that? Pretty much sells itself.</p>"
